      "to_id": "cec50b17:0",
      "content": "DONE — root cause found and fixed.\n\n**First error:** `SyntaxError: Identifier 'messagesList' has already been declared`\n\n**Lines responsible:**\n- Line 1449: `const messagesList = document.getElementById('messages-list');` (inside the tab-switching setup block)\n- Line 1555: `const messagesList = document.getElementById('messages-list');` (duplicate, inside the `// Render messages` comment block)\n\nThis duplicate `const` declaration in the same script scope is a syntax error that aborts the entire `<script>` block before execution begins — so `connect()` is never called, the SSE handler never fires, and `label.textContent` is never set to `'live'`. The page stays on \"Connecting…\" forever.\n\n**Fix applied:** Removed the duplicate declaration at line 1555. The variable is already in scope from line 1449.\n\n**File changed:** `public/index.html` only. No build step needed (static HTML). Not committed per instructions.",
